and expression, and picked up a book or some sewing, evidently waiting
impatiently for the intruder to go.
  She felt all the time as if she might at any moment penetrate that
on which- with a terrible questioning too great for her strength-
her spiritual gaze was fixed.
  One day toward the end of December Natasha, pale and thin, dressed
