his reflections. And experience tells us that power is not merely a
word but an actually existing phenomenon.
  Not to speak of the fact that no description of the collective
activity of men can do without the conception of power, the
existence of power is proved both by history and by observing
contemporary events.
  Whenever an event occurs a man appears or men appear, by whose
