him to be limited just because he is not conscious of it except as
free.
  You say: I am not and am not free. But I have lifted my hand and let
it fall. Everyone understands that this illogical reply is an
irrefutable demonstration of freedom.
  That reply is the expression of a consciousness that is not
subject to reason.
  If the consciousness of freedom were not a separate and
independent source of self-consciousness it would be subject to
reasoning and to experience, but in fact such subjection does not
exist and is inconceivable.
  A series of experiments and arguments proves to every man that he,
